BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 21 KYODO -- The Ministry of Agriculture, 
Forestry and Fisheries tentatively decided Saturday [21 May] to 
name a former vice agriculture minister for international 
affairs to head the ministry-affiliated Livestock Industry 
Promotion Corp., ministry officials said. 
  Jiro Shiwaku, 61, will officially succeed the current 
president, Nobuo Imamura, on June 1, the officials said. 
  Shiwaku represented Japan in the Uruguay Round of 
multilateral trade talks under the General Agreement on Tariffs 
and Trade, which were concluded last December. 

